using './main.bicep'

// ============================================================================
// Two required values — everything else is defaulted or created by the
// template itself.
//
// `tenantId` is inferred from the deployment context (subscription().tenantId).
// All operational tuning knobs (Search SKU, Foundry, Document Intelligence,
// Key Vault, processing modes, concurrency, backup schedule, file extensions,
// etc.) are hardcoded in main.bicep and can be tuned post-deployment via
// Function App settings.
// ============================================================================

// Resource-name prefix (3–16 chars, lowercase letters / digits / hyphens).
// A short uniqueness hash is appended automatically where Azure demands
// globally-unique names (Search / Foundry / DocIntel / Storage / Key Vault).
param baseName = 'sp-indexer'

// Leave as-is to use the resource group's region, or pin to a specific
// Azure AI Vision multimodal-4.0-supported region.
param location = 'swedencentral'

// The SharePoint site the connector will monitor.
// (Grant the Function's managed identity `Sites.Selected` on just this
//  site via infra/grant-site-permission.ps1 after deployment.)
param sharePointSiteUrl = 'https://yourcompany.sharepoint.com/sites/YourSite'

// ============================================================================
// Per-user security trimming — OPT-IN. Default false: Copilot Studio queries
// Azure AI Search directly as a Knowledge Source (simplest deployment).
// Flip to true only after reading the README's "Extending with Per-User
// Security Trimming" section — adding it requires the `Application
// Administrator` Entra role and a Power Platform connection setup.
// ============================================================================
// param enableSecurityTrimming = true

// Escape hatch — only relevant when enableSecurityTrimming = true. LEAVE
// EMPTY on the normal trimming path; the template will declare the
// /api/search Entra app registration itself via the Microsoft Graph Bicep
// extension. Only populate this when the deployer lacks Graph privileges
// and an admin has pre-created the app registration via
// infra/create-api-app-registration.ps1. Accepts a bare GUID or
// `api://<clientId>`.
// param apiAudience = '00000000-1111-2222-3333-444444444444'
